snippet.textDisplay: To everyone saying taylor just faulted responsibility to her ex for becoming an addict obviously doesn't know that she has taken responsibility. She has stated that she was an addict before she met her ex until he introduced her to her drug of choice. She had also made it clear that she made the choice to take the heroin and was not forced. She just came out about her abuse and how that played into her becoming an addict. As for the animals, she had 1 animal die from something other than old age or cancer (her reptile died from an electrical malfunction). The rest she rehomed. She has already admitted to taking in too many animals when she was being abused and most were rehomed when she went to rehab.

snippet.textDisplay: Suboxone really does work IF you want it to but that's just like anything though you have to want it to succeed. People always have the view that "oh why don't you just quit" or something stupid like that but they don't understand how hard it is to come out of an opiate addiction especially in her case where there's also a codependency with her BF (ex-bf) where they feed off each others addiction. I've been struggling with an opiate/heroin addiction for 7-8 years within that time only 2 years were spent sober thanks to suboxone and goin out  to the bush/mountains for hikes. The fact that she realizes why she became an addict, stayed and addict and also coming to terms with herself being honest deserves nothing less then great praise because again its easy to say "just quit" when your on the other aide of the mirror and haven't experienced it. Its a lot harder then everyone thinks! The whole thing with her ex, your right nobody can force someone to use OR can be blamed for someones use. Its all that individuals choice BUT there are environmental and social factors that lead to or prolong addiction like in her case the BF used and because of her insecurities and need for companionship made her susceptible, its no different then say a girl getting pressured to have sex for the first time by some guy just wanting to get laid.
